Author: David Vultur
Message:
Modal overlay height fixed

If on a smaller device,  (with the height 400px or less), that height of 125% will not cover all those `-100px` added. As the height of the screen would be, for eg: 200px, the height of the overlay would be 125% (250px), and the -100px would set only 150px on the screen, and 50px would be left with no overlay.
Demo of the bug: https://codepen.io/artur99/pen/qmpMYy
Demo of the fix: https://codepen.io/artur99/pen/ZKvMRy

Author: Emanuel Zienecker
Message:
Upgrade to jQuery v3

Goal was to migrate the project to jQuery v3.

Two issues have to been fixed.

1. jQuery.fn.bind() and jQuery.fn.unbind(): These methods have been
deprecated since jQuery v3.0 and they should be replaced with on() and
off(). Affected files: search.js, dropdown.js, sideNav.js, slider.js,
transitions.js.

2. jQuery.easing.easeOutQuart should use only first argument: the extra
parameters that the easing functions expected are now deprecated. Read
https://jquery.com/upgrade-guide/3.0/#deprecated-additional-easing-funct
ion-parameters for details. On https://github.com/gdsmith/jquery.easing
there is a newer version. Added jquery.easing with version 1.4. Update
Gruntfile.js to match the newer version.

Author: Johann Abraham
Message:
jump to the tabs and it was necessary to scroll down to see the tab content.

The reason for that was that the content for the previously active tab was being hidden before
the content for the next tab was being shown, which was shortening the document.

As a fix the next tab content is shown first before the old tab content is hidden.

If the tabs are much different lengths then the document will still be shortened and there will
still be some movement, but only if the bottom of the shorter tab is above the bottom of
the screen

BUG: textarea padding

When not using a prefix icon, there is too much
padding on the top. This is noticeable when two
textareas are side-by-side.

1) With no text, the placeholders line up, but
the lines are offset.
2) With text the labels match, but the written
text and the lines are offset.

Here's a code-pen with v0.97.6 showing the bug:
http://codepen.io/anon/pen/zBqGPB

I've also included the text-areas in the sample
test/html/forms.html for easier testing
